ena.description: [ID provided by the local context hub]

dwc.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations responsible for recording the original dwc:Occurrence. The primary collector or observer, especially one who applies a personal identifier (dwc:recordNumber), should be listed first.
A list (concatenated and separated) of geographic names less specific than the information captured in the dwc:locality term.
The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.
A list (concatenated and separated) of the globally unique identifier for the person, people, groups, or organizations responsible for recording the original dwc:Occurrence.

ena.description: 16-digit number that is compatible with the ISO Standard (ISO 27729),  if multiple IDs separate with a | and no spaces

dwc.description: An identifier for the dwc:MaterialSample (as opposed to a particular digital record of the dwc:MaterialSample). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the dwc:materialSampleID globally unique.
A common or vernacular name.

An identifier for the dwc:Occurrence (as opposed to a particular digital record of the dwc:Occurrence). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.
The date-time or interval during which a dwc:Event occurred. For occurrences, this is the date-time when the dwc:Event was recorded. Not suitable for a time in a geological context.

ena.description: YYYY-MM-DD, YYYY-MM, YYYY, NOT_COLLECTED or NOT_PROVIDED

dwc.description: The geographic latitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in dwc:geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a dcterms:Location. Positive values are north of the Equator, negative values are south of it. Legal values lie between -90 and 90, inclusive.

The geographic longitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in dwc:geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a dcterms:Location. Positive values are east of the Greenwich Meridian, negative values are west of it. Legal values lie between -180 and 180, inclusive.
The original description of the depth below the local surface.

mixs.description: The vertical distance below local surface. For sediment or soil samples depth is measured from sediment or soil surface, respectively. Depth can be reported as an interval for subsurface samples

dwc.description: The original description of the elevation (altitude, usually above sea level) of the Location.

ena.description: filename (including ".pdf" extension) if permit is required or NOT_APPLICABLE if permit is not required

dwc.description: The full scientific name of the family in which the dwc:Taxon is classified.
The full scientific name of the genus in which the dwc:Taxon is classified.
Notes or comments about the spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalized in the method referred to in dwc:georeferenceProtocol.
A category or description of the habitat in which the dwc:Event occurred.

mixs.description: Original body habitat where the sample was obtained from

dwc.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who assigned the dwc:Taxon to the subject.
The name of the lowest or terminal infraspecific epithet of the dwc:scientificName, excluding any rank designation.
The age class or life stage of the dwc:Organism(s) at the time the dwc:Occurrence was recorded.

ena.description: filename (including ".pdf" extension) if permit is required or NOT_APPLICABLE if permit is not required

dwc.description: The full scientific name of the order in which the dwc:Taxon is classified.
A description of the kind of dwc:Organism instance. Can be used to indicate whether the dwc:Organism instance represents a discrete organism or if it represents a particular type of aggregation.
The date-time or interval during which a dwc:Event occurred. For occurrences, this is the date-time when the dwc:Event was recorded. Not suitable for a time in a geological context.

ena.description: Date as YYYY, YYYY-MM or YYYY-MM-DD

dwc.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of preparations and preservation methods for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
Comments or notes about the relationship between the two resources.

mixs.description: Description of relationship(s) between the subject organism and other organism(s) it is associated with. E.g., parasite on species X; mutualist with species Y. The target organism is the subject of the relationship, and the other organism(s) is the object

dwc.description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

ena.description: 16-digit number that is compatible with the ISO Standard (ISO 27729), if multiple IDs separate with a | and no spaces
filename (including ".pdf" extension) if permit is required or NOT_APPLICABLE if permit is not required

dwc.description: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of a dwc:Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in the dwc:identificationQualifier term.
An identifier given to the dwc:Event in the field. Often serves as a link between field notes and the dwc:Event.
The sex of the biological individual(s) represented in the dwc:Occurrence.
A numeric value for a measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling dwc:Event.

An identifier for the dwc:MaterialSample (as opposed to a particular digital record of the dwc:MaterialSample). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the dwc:materialSampleID globally unique.

mixs.description: The taxonomic name of the organism(s) found living in mutualistic, commensalistic, or parasitic symbiosis with the specific host. The sampled symbiont can have its own symbionts. For example, parasites may have hyperparasites (=parasites of the parasite)

dwc.description: An identifier for the set of dwc:Taxon information. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

mixs.description: NCBI taxon id of the sample.  Maybe be a single taxon or mixed taxa sample. Use 'synthetic metagenome  for mock community/positive controls, or 'blank sample' for negative controls

dwc.description: Comments or notes about the taxon or name.
The time or interval during which a dwc:Event occurred.

ena.description: 24-hour format with hours and minutes separated by colon
